      <title>Chaos Reborn Kickstarter Launched</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/news/2014/3/18/chaos-reborn-kickstarter-launched/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 18 Mar 2014 06:51:48 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/news/2014/3/18/chaos-reborn-kickstarter-launched/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/2014-03-18-2014318chaos-reborn-kickstarter-launched/image-asset.jpeg&#34; alt=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;After about a year of building a prototype and refining the systems, Julian&#xA;Gollop has launched a Kickstarter for &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/1206403106/chaos-reborn-from-the-creator-of-the-original-x-co&#34;&gt;&amp;ldquo;Chaos Reborn&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt;. Gollop has&#xA;created many brilliant games over the years - &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.worldofspectrum.org/infoseekid.cgi?id=0004058&#34;&gt;&amp;ldquo;Rebelstar&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.worldofspectrum.org/infoseekid.cgi?id=0002813&#34;&gt;&amp;ldquo;Laser&#xA;Squad&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.lemonamiga.com/games/details.php?id=3299&#34;&gt;&amp;ldquo;X-Com&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt; to name a few - and now he&amp;rsquo;s returning to one&#xA;of his first, [&amp;ldquo;Chaos&amp;rdquo;][131]. It will be a turn based affair, set in a fantasy&#xA;realm with magic and unique creatures, and will feature a variety of&#xA;multiplayer modes.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
